VimpelCom Ltd. (VIP)  has cut international
roaming charges for mobile  Internet access  as much as 96
percent, the last of  Russia â€™s three biggest mobile operators to
lower fees, Vedomosti said.  One megabyte of data sent or received in  Europe  at the
discounted rate will cost 30.21 rubles ($1.02) from as much as
768 rubles previously, the newspaper said, citing VimpelCom.
Rates were also reduced in  Southeast Asia , according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
